Zadanie 10 - CI/CD, Docker, Sonar, deployment, BrowserStack

Aplikacja: 5/server (Go) + 5/client (React), bot Kotlin (3), testy E2E (6/e2e)

| Punkt | Opis | Folder |
|-------|------|--------|
| 3.0 | Instancje Docker (serwer + klient) | 10/3.0/ |
| 3.5 | Pipeline GitHub Actions (build, fatjar) | 10/3.5/ |
| 4.0 | Notyfikacja mailowa wyników Sonar | 10/4.0/ |
| 4.5 | Deployment na chmurę (klient + serwer) | 10/4.5/ |
| 5.0 | Testy regresyjne BrowserStack w Actions | 10/5.0/ |

## Uruchomienie Docker (3.0)

```powershell
cd 10\3.0
docker compose up --build
```

Klient: http://localhost:5173, serwer: http://localhost:8080

## Wdrożenie pipeline (3.5-5.0)

```powershell
.\10\5.0\apply.ps1
```

Kopiuje workflow do `.github/workflows/ebiz-pipeline.yml`.

## Sekrety GitHub

| Sekret | Opis |
|--------|------|
| SONAR_TOKEN | Token SonarCloud |
| MAIL_SERVER | Host SMTP |
| MAIL_PORT | Port SMTP (np. 587) |
| MAIL_USERNAME | Login SMTP |
| MAIL_PASSWORD | Hasło SMTP |
| MAIL_TO | Adres odbiorcy |
| DOCKERHUB_USERNAME | Login Docker Hub |
| DOCKERHUB_TOKEN | Token Docker Hub |
| DEPLOY_HOST | Adres VM (np. user@1.2.3.4) |
| DEPLOY_SSH_KEY | Klucz prywatny SSH |
| DEPLOY_URL | URL klienta po deploy (np. http://1.2.3.4:5173) |
| BROWSERSTACK_USERNAME | Login BrowserStack |
| BROWSERSTACK_ACCESS_KEY | Klucz BrowserStack |
